[assistant] Fixed the failing test.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - `addRequestSpecification(otherSpecification)` invokes `SpecificationMerger.merge(...)`, which overwrites request fields including `baseUri`, `port`, and `basePath`.
[assistant] - Since the test set the server connection details before calling `addRequestSpecification(...)`, they were overwritten by defaults from `otherSpecification`, causing Rest Assured to connect to the wrong endpoint and fail with `Connection refused`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Moved `.setBaseUri(...)`, `.setPort(...)`, and `.setBasePath(...)` after `.addRequestSpecification(otherSpecification)` in:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/SpecificationMergerInner_mergeConfig_closure1Test.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] This keeps the merge path covered while ensuring the final request points to the test server.
